# Filtering groups, pivot & unpivot

## Filtering groups — no `HAVING` keyword

- Chain **`.filter()` after `.agg()`**:
  - `groupBy("c").agg(_sum("x").alias("t")).filter(col("t") > 100)`

## Pivot — distinct values → columns

- **Always pass the value list explicitly**: `pivot("col", [...])`
- Skips the discovery scan and **locks the output column order**

## Unpivot — columns → rows (inverse)

- **`stack(n, ...)`** via `selectExpr` — all 3.x
- **`df.unpivot(...)`** / **`df.melt(...)`** — Spark 3.4+ (pandas-familiar)
